  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Multi-Sector East Ghouta and Afrin Response (MEAR)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Multi-Sector East Ghouta and Afrin Response (MEAR) targets over 28,000 individuals with a combination of WASH, shelter and protection activities targeted towards IDPs from East Ghouta and Afrin. Based on the current situation, the project has been designed to address the urgent and life-saving needs in targeted locations. However, the situation is changing rapidly, especially in Afrin and ADRA remains committed to serving the most vulnerable wherever they are located. ADRA Syria is currently working on the response in both areas (response to East Ghouta and Afrin) and has the necessary permissions to implement the planned activities in a short space of time.</narrative>
  </description>
